                                  INSTALLATION

Just type "./waf configure", followed by "./waf install".
This will install all the necessary files in your home directory.
Other directories can be specified by calling waf with the prefix
variable, for example, "./waf configure --prefix=/usr".

                                  REQUIREMENTS

For configuring, building and installing you need waf.

Also you will need the DBus, Glade, GObject, GTK and XDG Python modules.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* python-dbus
* python-glade2
* python-gobject
* python-gtk2
* python-xdg

                               BUILD REQUIREMENTS

You will need the gettext and intltool tools.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* gettext
* intltool

